• Failure to enroll or other truancy: a child (age 6) is not enrolled
in school or a pattern of keeping a school-age child home for
nonlegitimate reasons (e.g., to work and to care for siblings)
an average of at least 3 days a month

[p. <i>125</i>] | [<a href="psyc.get.jpg.aspx?display=page&amp;legacyid=1000334627-I00145&amp;api=new&amp;maxwidth=700">Page Image</a>]<br />

• Unmet special education needs: child fails to receive recommended
remedial educational services or treatment for his or
her diagnosed learning disorder or other special educational
needs of the child
<table>
<tr><td>
<p>
• Special needs that are unmet can lead to long-term consequences
for children. An educational specialist is usually
needed to document this condition as neglect.
</p>
</td></tr>
</table>


• Special needs that are unmet can lead to long-term consequences
for children. An educational specialist is usually
